4 Section 2. Section 87-2-130, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "87-2-130. Aquatic invasive species prevention pass. (1) Except as provided in 87-2-803(6), to be
6 eligible to fish in Montana or to apply for a fishing license or a combination license that includes a fishing
7 license, a person who is 16 years of age or older must first obtain an aquatic invasive species prevention pass
8 as provided in this section. The pass must be purchased once each license year.
9 (2) Resident aquatic invasive species prevention passes may be purchased for a fee of $2 $2.50.
10 (3) Nonresident aquatic invasive species prevention passes may be purchased for a fee of $7.50."
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective March 1, 2026.
